OL,3,CWould a four-week summer school
OL,4,Choliday work?
OL,6,FThe proposal
OL,8,FProfessor Major suggests that the
OL,9,Fschool calendar has been stuck in in
OL,10,Fplace since "Victorian times", and
OL,11,Fthat research shows spreading holidays
OL,12,Facross the year might improve the
OL,13,Fworking lives of teachers by making
OL,14,Fterm lengths more equal.
OL,16,FIt would involve shortening the summer
OL,17,Fholiday and introducing a two-week
OL,18,Fautumn half-term, following a similar
OL,19,Fproposal made by the Welsh government
OL,20,Ffor the academic year of 2025-2026.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G3/19
