OL,3,CWould a four-week summer school
OL,4,Choliday work?
OL,6,FProfessor Major said that many look at
OL,7,Fthe summer holidays as "idyllic" with
OL,8,F"rose-tinted glasses" on, but studies
OL,9,Fsuggest that children lose learning
OL,10,Fover such an extended period.
OL,12,F"Often children get bored during those
OL,13,Fsix weeks, and also, wellbeing is a
OL,14,Fconcern," he said.
OL,16,F"I do a lot of work around
OL,17,Fsafeguarding. And if (as a teacher),
OL,18,Fyou've got a child that you're keeping
OL,19,Fan eye on, and they've gone for six
OL,20,Fweeks, it really plays on your mind."
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G7/19
